Adhere to this structure:

src/
├── api/
│   ├── generated/   # @hey-api/openapi-ts generated files (DO NOT EDIT MANUALLY)
│   └── model/       # Manual Zod schemas (if not generated)
├── components/
│   ├── ui/          # Chakra-based reusable UI wrappers/extensions
│   ├── features/    # Domain-specific components
│   └── layout/      # Layout wrappers (Header, Sidebar, Page shell)
├── hooks/           # Custom hooks (non-API)
├── lib/             # Utility libraries (Zod, DOMPurify, formatters)
├── locales/         # i18n configurations
├── routes/          # TanStack Router file routes
├── stores/          # React Contexts (Theme, Auth)
├── types/           # Global TypeScript types (that are not API models)
└── main.tsx         # Entry point

# Response Guidelines for AI
1.  **Thinking Process:** Briefly explain the architectural choice, citing specific rules, as comments in files.
2.  **Code generation:** Include necessary imports. Prefer Chakra UI components and style props; use Tailwind only for layout utilities.
3.  **Refactoring:** Prioritize removing `useEffect` for data fetching, adopting `useOptimistic`, and leveraging generated API client functions.
4.  **Dependencies:** If a new library is needed, suggest installing via `pnpm add`.